summary: Filtering search feature in the Add bookmark / bookmark item editing dialog
comments:
User Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (X11; Fedora; Linux x86_64; rv:69.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/69.0

Steps to reproduce:

Add a bookmark, with ctrl+D or the star icon.


Actual results:

It lets me choose a folder, with a dropdown arrow to choose more folders, but there is no clearly discoverable way to search (and no filtering search at all, only typeahead which is a geeky undiscoverable feature)


Expected results:

Show a filtering search bar above the listview of bookmark folders, just like the search bar you already have in the bookmarks sidebar or in the bookmarks library dialog (Ctrl+shift+O, which actually is conflicting, but that's bug #1606842).

Filtering search is not the same as typeahead (which is undiscoverable, error-prone, single-targetting instead of allowing to drill down on multiple possibilities).
